text: The Robinson-Smith House was built in 1909. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2016. It is American Foursquare in style. It was built by Glenn Charles McAlister (1873-1961), who was a self-trained architect. With 15 photos from 2015. ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Sheridan County, Wyoming Category:American Foursquare architecture in Wyoming Category:Houses completed in 1909
title: Robinson-Smith House
